column46: study_description

The purpose of this study is to establish whether intestinal organoid cultures from IBD patients are a good model of disease by studying various disease phenomena including%2C epithelial repair%2C wound healing%2C fibrotic changes%2C granulomas and inflammatory processes. Organoids will be used for target pertubation and validation studies. %0D%0AThis data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria)%2C please see http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanger.ac.uk%2Fdatasharing%2F
